# AoE2.ai Project Conventions

## Stack
- Next.js 15 App Router with `output: "standalone"`
- TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- OpenAI Responses API for AI features
- SQLite + Prisma 7 for persistence
- NextAuth.js for authentication

## Localization
- All user-facing pages live under `src/app/[locale]/` (`en`/`es`)
- Translations in `src/i18n/dictionaries/{en,es}.json` — keep both in sync
- AI prompts are locale-aware via `runtime.ts` — update `getLocaleInstruction()` when adding AoE2 terminology
- Metadata uses `buildPageMetadata()` from `src/lib/seo.ts`

## API Routes
- All API routes must include rate limiting from `src/lib/rate-limit.ts`
- AI routes require authentication via `getServerSession(authOptions)`
- Streaming routes must use `TransformStream` (not `ReadableStream.start()`) and set `X-Accel-Buffering: no`

## Components
- Client components use `"use client"` directive
- AI features gated with `useRequireAuth()` hook
- Use `lucide-react` for icons

## Database
- Schema in `prisma/schema.prisma`; when adding tables, also add the `CREATE TABLE` SQL to `ensureDatabase()` in `src/lib/prisma.ts`
- Import client from `@/lib/prisma`, never instantiate `PrismaClient` directly

## Environment
- Never commit `.env` — secrets go in GitHub Secrets for production
- Public env vars prefixed with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`
